#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:451
msgid "<emphasis>Figure: Web services change.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:455
msgid ""
"Like the other Generic Interface configuration screens such as Network "
"Transport, Operation, Invoker and Mapping, the initial configuration (add)  "
"screen will only present two options: \"Save\" and \"Cancel\". If the "
"configuration is re-visited, a new option \"Save and Finish\" will appear.  "
"The behavior of this feature is defined below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:462
msgid ""
"\"Save\" will store the current configuration level in the database and it "
"will return to the previous screen to review your changes or to configure "
"deeper settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:467
msgid ""
"\"Save and Finish\" will store the current configuration level in the "
"database and it will return to the previous screen in the configuration "
"hierarchy (to the immediate upper configuration level)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:472
msgid ""
"\"Cancel\" will discard any configuration change to the current "
"configuration level and will return to the previous screen in the "
"configuration hierarchy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot><screeninfo>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:478
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:494
msgid "Web Service Provider Network Transport"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:480
msgid ""
"In future the list of available network transports will be increased. "
"Currently only the \"HTTP::SOAP\" transport is available. Each transport has "
"different configuration options to setup and they might use different "
"frontend modules to configure it, but mostly they should look similar to the "
"\"HTTP::SOAP\" transport configuration module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:486
msgid ""
"It is quite simple to configure the \"HTTP::SOAP\" protocol as provider.  "
"There are only two settings: \"Namespace\" and \"Maximum message length\". "
"These fields are required. The first one is a URI to give SOAP methods a "
"context, reducing ambiguities, and the second one is a field where you can "
"specify the maximum size (in bytes) for SOAP messages that OTRS will process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:494
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screeninfo\" id=\"0\"/> <graphic srccredit=\"Adminarea "
"web service provider network transport - screenshot\" scale=\"40\" fileref="
"\"screenshots/genericinterface-webservice-provider-transport.png\"></graphic>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:499
msgid "<emphasis>Figure: Web service provider network transport.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot><screeninfo>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:504
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:539
msgid "Web Service Operation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:506
msgid ""
"The actions that can be performed when you are using OTRS as a provider are "
"called \"Operations\". Each operation belongs to a controller. Controllers "
"are collections of operations or invokers, normally operations from the same "
"controller need similar settings and share the same configuration dialog. "
"But each operation can have independent configuration dialogues if needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:513
msgid ""
"Name, Description, Backend, and Mappings are fields that normally appear on "
"every operation, other special fields can appear in non default "
"configuration dialogues to fulfill specific needs of the operation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:518
msgid ""
"Normally there are two mapping configuration sections on each operation, one "
"for the incoming data and another one for the outgoing data. You can choose "
"different mapping types (backends) for each mapping direction, since their "
"configuration is independent from each other and also independent from the "
"operation backend. The normal and most common practice is that the operation "
"uses the same mapping type in both cases (with inverted configuration). The "
"complete mapping configuration is done in a separate screen which depends on "
"the mapping type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:527
msgid ""
"The operation backend is pre-populated and is not editable. You will see "
"this parameter when you choose the operation on the web service edit screen. "
"The field is only informative."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:531
msgid ""
"In the left part of the screen on the action column you have the options: "
"\"Go back to web service\" (discarding all changes since the last save) and "
"\"Delete\". If you click on the last one, a dialog will open and ask you if "
"you like to remove the operation. Click on \"Delete\" button to confirm the "
"removal of the operation and it configuration or \"Cancel\" to close the "
"delete dialog."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:539
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screeninfo\" id=\"0\"/> <graphic srccredit=\"Adminarea "
"web service operation - screenshot\" scale=\"40\" fileref=\"screenshots/"
"genericinterface-webservice-operation.png\"></graphic>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:544
msgid "<emphasis>Figure: Web service operation.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot><screeninfo>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:549
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:602
msgid "Web Service Requester Network Transport"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:551
msgid ""
"The network transport configuration for the requester is similar to the "
"configuration for the provider. For the Requester \"HTTP::SOAP\" network "
"transport there are more fields to be set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:556
msgid ""
"Apart from the \"Endpoint\" (URI of the Remote System web service interface "
"to accept requests) and \"Namespace\" which are required fields, you can "
"also specify:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:563
msgid ""
"Encoding (such as utf-8, latin1, iso-8859-1, cp1250, etc) for the SOAP "
"message."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:569
msgid ""
"SOAPAction Header: you can use this to send an empty or filled SOAPAction "
"header.  Set to \"No\" and the SOAPAction header on the SOAP message will be "
"an empty string, or set to \"Yes\" to send the soap action in "
"Namespace#Action format and define the separator (typically \"/\" for .Net "
"web services and \"#\" for the rest)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:578
msgid ""
"Authentication: to set the authentication mechanism, set to \"-\" to not use "
"any authentication or select one from the list and the detail fields will "
"appear."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:586
msgid ""
"Currently only the \"BasicAuth\" (HTTP) authentication mechanism is "
"implemented.  You can decide whether or not to use it depending on the "
"Remote System configuration. If used, you must provide the User Name and the "
"Password to access the remote system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><warning><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:594
msgid ""
"If you supply a password for authentication and after you export the web "
"service to a YAML file this password will be revealed and will be written "
"into a plain text string inside the YAML file. Be aware of it and take "
"precautions if needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-gui.xml:602
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screeninfo\" id=\"0\"/> <graphic srccredit=\"Adminarea "
"web service requester network transport - screenshot\" scale=\"40\" fileref="
"\"screenshots/genericinterface-webservice-requester-transport.png\"></"
"graphic>"
